ndemned by his children, more so by the sons he cherishes.\n\n- Janvier Chouteu-Chando, Disciples of Fortune\n|\nOh mommy! You are my world, my love. I am your little boy, and I stole your heart.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nDon’t worry, Miss Brielle. To be honest, the ones with a little bit of crazy have always been my favorite.\n\n- C.J. Milbrandt, Into the Hills: A Zane Johns Adventure\n|\nEveryone you have ever loved in your life becomes a part of your soul. They never leave. They're always inside you, and you can bring them out whenever you want.\n\n- Nate Kenyon, Sparrow Rock\n|\nEverybody’s gotta learn, nobody’s born knowing.\n\n- Harper\n|\nEquality and freedom are not luxuries to lightly cast aside. Without them, order cannot long endure before approaching depths beyond imagining.\n\n- Alan Moore, V for Vendetta\n|\nThe Bible has noble poetry in it... and some good morals and a wealth of obscenity, and upwards of a thousand lies.\n\n- Mark\n|\nI might love my e-reader, but I'd never pass up the chance to browse real books.\n\n- Nichole Chase, Suddenly Royal\n|\nLove has no limitations. It cannot be measured. It has no boundaries. Although many have tried, love is indefinable.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nFriendship is unnecessary, like philosophy, like art.... It has no survival value; rather it is one of those things which give value to survival.\n\n- C.S. Lewis, The Four Loves\n|\nI love you' means I want you to be happy.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Slaying Dragons\n|\nLove gives you knees to crawl, feet to run, legs to sprint, and wings to soar.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nAnd now I am here, as alone as I've ever been. I am seventeen years old. This is not how it's suppose to be. This is not how my life is suppose to turn out.\n\n- Gayle Forman, If I Stay\n|\nA true friend unbosoms freely, advises justly, assists readily, adventures boldly, takes all patiently, defends courageously, and continues a friend unchangeably\n\n- William\n|\nWhen you live